1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:36,350 --> 00:01:42,229
[I Don't Want to Be Friends With You]

3
00:01:46,759 --> 00:01:47,690
Pick one!

4
00:01:48,080 --> 00:01:49,390
Pick?

5
00:01:49,470 --> 00:01:50,340
Yes!

6
00:01:50,430 --> 00:01:51,630
One is lettuce and ham,

7
00:01:51,720 --> 00:01:53,259
the other is chicken and corn.

8
00:01:53,509 --> 00:01:54,780
I'd rather have both.

9
00:01:55,190 --> 00:01:56,070
No, no, no.

10
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,700
You can't have both of them.

11
00:01:57,789 --> 00:01:58,930
You have to choose one.

12
00:01:59,280 --> 00:02:00,220
But I want them both.

13
00:02:00,310 --> 00:02:01,210
Why?

14
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:02,390
Just because you made them.

15
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:03,380
I don't want to choose.

16
00:02:03,510 --> 00:02:04,390
I want both.

17
00:02:06,150 --> 00:02:07,140
Eat them both, then.

18
00:02:07,230 --> 00:02:08,370
Don't leave anything.

19
00:02:09,030 --> 00:02:09,110
[Episode 13: I Want Both the Fish
and the Bear Palm]

20
00:02:09,110 --> 00:02:09,750
You can have them.

21
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:10,750
I'm not eating.

22
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:11,720
You can have them.

23
00:02:15,480 --> 00:02:16,360
Xiao,

24
00:02:16,920 --> 00:02:17,980
are you okay?

25
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:24,630
Why are you fighting in that age?

26
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:25,940
Why don't you use your brain?

27
00:02:27,310 --> 00:02:28,340
I said,

28
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:30,140
if he dared to bully you again,

29
00:02:30,230 --> 00:02:32,210
I must warn him.

30
00:02:32,350 --> 00:02:34,690
Now you should look at yourself?

31
00:02:35,350 --> 00:02:36,970
I don't leave him in an easy circumstance.

32
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:42,450
It's a little hard!

33
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:44,770
And who do you support?

34
00:02:59,430 --> 00:03:01,020
You two, with black eyes, stand up!

35
00:03:07,910 --> 00:03:08,430
What's the matter?

36
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:09,400
Do you fight with each other?

37
00:03:12,270 --> 00:03:13,580
I fell into the pit while I was walking.

38
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:14,620
How about you?

39
00:03:14,710 --> 00:03:15,180
I

40
00:03:15,270 --> 00:03:16,890
fell down the stairs while I was working.

41
00:03:17,079 --> 00:03:18,340
You both fell down.

42
00:03:18,430 --> 00:03:19,660
Go to my office after class,

43
00:03:19,750 --> 00:03:20,630
and now sit down.

44
00:03:49,270 --> 00:03:49,870
Drink it?

45
00:03:49,950 --> 00:03:57,650
I didn't beat them.

46
00:04:02,320 --> 00:04:03,500
You can't believe me,

47
00:04:03,640 --> 00:04:05,330
but I can't take the blame.

48
00:04:06,070 --> 00:04:07,610
My dad told me when he was still alive,

49
00:04:07,870 --> 00:04:09,670
the worst thing was to beat women.

50
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:11,170
I can't do that.

51
00:04:11,910 --> 00:04:12,790
Your dad

52
00:04:13,470 --> 00:04:14,350
passed away.

53
00:04:17,950 --> 00:04:19,019
I lost my father and mother.

54
00:04:19,870 --> 00:04:22,570
My hometown was flooded when I was seven,

55
00:04:22,950 --> 00:04:24,450
and they went to relieve
the victims of the flood.

56
00:04:24,910 --> 00:04:26,530
There was a car accident on the road,

57
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:28,730
and both of them died.

58
00:04:31,750 --> 00:04:33,370
What did your parents do?

59
00:04:34,150 --> 00:04:35,450
My father was a soldier,

60
00:04:35,960 --> 00:04:36,840
a military doctor.

61
00:04:37,470 --> 00:04:39,330
He opened a clinic after he retired.

62
00:04:39,670 --> 00:04:41,380
He was willing to help others,

63
00:04:41,990 --> 00:04:43,530
but during his helping
process, he lost his own life.

64
00:04:45,630 --> 00:04:46,690
My father is also a soldier.

65
00:04:47,080 --> 00:04:48,300
That's the way they are,

66
00:04:49,640 --> 00:04:51,090
always caring for others

67
00:04:51,280 --> 00:04:52,730
but not themselves.

68
00:04:55,880 --> 00:04:58,450
So now you live with your younger uncle?

69
00:05:00,230 --> 00:05:01,110
Yes.

70
00:05:01,870 --> 00:05:03,770
Only my younger uncle
is willing to support me.

71
00:05:04,870 --> 00:05:06,220
Because of me,

72
00:05:06,630 --> 00:05:08,450
he never got married.

73
00:05:09,200 --> 00:05:10,570
I feel sorry for him.

74
00:05:10,670 --> 00:05:13,070
You need to be a good
person to reward him.

75
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:14,940
Why do you make trouble everywhere?

76
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:18,550
How do I get into trouble?

77
00:05:18,630 --> 00:05:19,510
Sure,

78
00:05:19,630 --> 00:05:20,940
I've done some bad things,

79
00:05:21,030 --> 00:05:22,630
but I didn't hurt anyone, right?

80
00:05:22,710 --> 00:05:24,580
If Li Jin Bu hadn't
ratted me out to my uncle

81
00:05:24,670 --> 00:05:25,550
and caused me to drop out,

82
00:05:25,950 --> 00:05:27,290
I wouldn't argue with her.

83
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:29,340
Who knew it'd come to this?

84
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:36,280
My watch?

85
00:05:36,550 --> 00:05:37,100
What watch?

86
00:05:37,190 --> 00:05:38,460
The one my father gave me.

87
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:41,020
Have you found your watch?

88
00:05:46,990 --> 00:05:48,530
Your bruises are symmetrical.

89
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:50,300
What's the matter?

90
00:05:50,390 --> 00:05:51,409
We tripped.

91
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:53,110
You're pretty good at tripping.

92
00:05:53,190 --> 00:05:54,610
Let me see you trip again.

93
00:05:58,080 --> 00:06:00,170
Mum.

94
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:02,180
Mum,

95
00:06:02,270 --> 00:06:05,230
I want to eat canned food.

96
00:06:05,320 --> 00:06:07,670
I want to eat cream cake.

97
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:10,850
I still want to eat steamed stuffed buns.

98
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:13,810
Mum.

99
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:23,210
I just had an operation,

100
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:25,850
but no one's here to keep me company.

101
00:06:26,270 --> 00:06:28,370
What kind of affection is this?

102
00:06:34,720 --> 00:06:35,420
Are you

103
00:06:35,510 --> 00:06:36,810
okay?

104
00:06:41,640 --> 00:06:42,650
I'm okay.

105
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:47,490
I'm okay. I'm okay.

106
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:50,110
Since you're fine,

107
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:50,940
I'll go now.

108
00:06:51,030 --> 00:06:53,370
No, why do you just get there and leave?

109
00:06:54,550 --> 00:06:56,090
I just came here to see you.

110
00:06:56,400 --> 00:06:57,500
If you are okay,

111
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:59,050
I'll go.

112
00:07:01,320 --> 00:07:03,330
If I had known, I would
have said something wrong.

113
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:07,700
What do you want to eat?

114
00:07:08,510 --> 00:07:09,580
I'll buy it for you.

115
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:11,850
I want to eat canned food.

116
00:07:38,430 --> 00:07:39,370
Sorry.

117
00:07:48,030 --> 00:07:48,980
It is for you.

118
00:07:49,350 --> 00:07:50,530
Wipe it quickly!

119
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:51,820
It is black.

120
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:53,610
Thank you.

121
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:57,490
You are not allowed to fight anymore.

122
00:07:57,590 --> 00:07:59,540
If you do that again, I will ignore you.

123
00:08:00,910 --> 00:08:01,940
Do you hear that?

124
00:08:02,080 --> 00:08:02,960
Yes.

125
00:08:05,390 --> 00:08:06,300
Are your legs okay?

126
00:08:06,390 --> 00:08:07,290
Fine.

127
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:09,170
Then you should go with slower steps.

128
00:08:14,110 --> 00:08:15,010
Where is Li Qing Tong?

129
00:08:21,390 --> 00:08:23,010
You come to see her.

130
00:08:25,110 --> 00:08:26,180
Where is she?

131
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:27,610
She went to the bathroom.

132
00:08:34,909 --> 00:08:35,780
How many times have I told you?

133
00:08:35,870 --> 00:08:38,150
Don't eat raw or cold food
for 24 hours after surgery.

134
00:08:38,230 --> 00:08:39,650
You still let her eat canned food.

135
00:08:39,799 --> 00:08:41,789
Are you treating her health as a joke?

136
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:42,470
Yes,

137
00:08:42,559 --> 00:08:43,610
we are wrong.

138
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:45,490
I didn't take care of her.

139
00:08:46,030 --> 00:08:46,870
Tell her

140
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:47,660
not to be greedy.

141
00:08:47,750 --> 00:08:49,450
Okay, thank you.

142
00:08:57,230 --> 00:08:58,370
Did it hurt anymore?

143
00:08:59,280 --> 00:09:00,330
No.

144
00:09:00,550 --> 00:09:01,610
Auntie.

145
00:09:02,310 --> 00:09:03,370
Sorry,

146
00:09:03,830 --> 00:09:05,540
I bought her the canned food.

147
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:07,550
I didn't know she couldn't eat that.

148
00:09:07,640 --> 00:09:08,690
It doesn't matter.

149
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:10,620
Your intention is kind.

150
00:09:10,750 --> 00:09:12,060
It's her own fault.

151
00:09:12,310 --> 00:09:13,610
She's too gluttonous.

152
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:16,910
I'll never eat canned food again.

153
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:17,930
Tong.

154
00:09:22,030 --> 00:09:22,970
Auntie.

155
00:09:23,110 --> 00:09:23,860
Sorry,

156
00:09:23,950 --> 00:09:25,070
I was supposed to come to see
Tong when the class was over,

157
00:09:25,160 --> 00:09:26,420
but my mum asked me to purchase something.

158
00:09:26,510 --> 00:09:27,390
It's all right.

159
00:09:28,190 --> 00:09:29,070
Li Qing Tong,

160
00:09:29,710 --> 00:09:31,210
guess what I bought for you?

161
00:09:31,350 --> 00:09:32,420
Canned food.

162
00:09:45,870 --> 00:09:46,750
What's up?

163
00:09:47,110 --> 00:09:48,410
There's no money left.

164
00:09:49,470 --> 00:09:51,030
The hospital fee hasn't been
paid back to our daughter yet.

165
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:52,570
What can we do in the future?

166
00:09:52,710 --> 00:09:53,670
Lower voice.

167
00:09:53,760 --> 00:09:54,780
Dahua is at home.

168
00:09:54,870 --> 00:09:56,690
Don't let her hear that.

169
00:09:59,270 --> 00:10:00,930
That's not enough.

170
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:02,350
Well,

171
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:04,500
you talk to the leader of your unit,

172
00:10:04,590 --> 00:10:06,330
and get a few months' salary in advance.

173
00:10:07,430 --> 00:10:09,010
Advance?

174
00:10:09,190 --> 00:10:11,290
This month's salary may be inaccessible.

175
00:10:11,830 --> 00:10:13,660
What's wrong with your unit?

176
00:10:15,230 --> 00:10:16,860
My unit is on the verge of bankruptcy.

177
00:10:37,270 --> 00:10:39,250
It's so much trouble to go to the toilet.

178
00:10:44,430 --> 00:10:45,390
You are

179
00:10:45,480 --> 00:10:47,370
Mr Li's daughter, aren't you?

180
00:10:47,710 --> 00:10:49,170
Uncle Wang.

181
00:10:49,990 --> 00:10:51,580
I haven't seen you in over a year.

182
00:10:51,670 --> 00:10:53,260
You've grown up a lot.

183
00:10:54,280 --> 00:10:55,100
What's...

184
00:10:55,190 --> 00:10:56,180
What's wrong with you?

185
00:10:56,270 --> 00:10:57,730
Why are you here?

186
00:10:58,070 --> 00:10:59,610
Appendicitis, just a minor surgery.

187
00:11:00,830 --> 00:11:02,900
Why are you in the
hospital early in the morning?

188
00:11:02,990 --> 00:11:04,210
You didn't go to work?

189
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:05,750
No,

190
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:07,540
the factory was closed.

191
00:11:07,630 --> 00:11:08,270
So,

192
00:11:08,360 --> 00:11:09,470
I'm here

193
00:11:09,560 --> 00:11:11,340
to take some medicine for
rheumatism to your auntie.

194
00:11:12,520 --> 00:11:14,130
The factory was closed?

195
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:18,050
That's the cement factory.

196
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:20,530
It has been closed for
more than half a year.

197
00:11:21,150 --> 00:11:22,030
Didn't your father

198
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:23,810
tell you about it?

199
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:26,010
Well, then.

200
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:26,750
Girl,

201
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:28,500
I'll make a move now.

202
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:36,990
Hua.

203
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:38,180
Have a meal.

204
00:11:42,430 --> 00:11:42,980
Auntie.

205
00:11:43,070 --> 00:11:44,060
My mum asked me to send
this to you.

206
00:11:44,150 --> 00:11:45,350
I forgot to pass it to you yesterday.

207
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:46,460
What's that?

208
00:11:46,550 --> 00:11:48,180
She mailed me the living expenses.

209
00:11:48,790 --> 00:11:50,210
I can't take it,

210
00:11:50,350 --> 00:11:52,260
and we can afford your meal.

211
00:11:52,550 --> 00:11:53,230
You misunderstand.

212
00:11:53,310 --> 00:11:54,790
She's here for you.

213
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:56,030
In my purse, I'll waste it.

214
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:56,910
You take it,

215
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:58,570
and use it to look after us.

216
00:12:04,950 --> 00:12:05,420
So,

217
00:12:05,510 --> 00:12:06,150
Hua,

218
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:07,620
I'll safekeep it for you.

219
00:12:07,710 --> 00:12:09,890
Then when you need to,
you can ask me for money.

220
00:12:10,720 --> 00:12:11,620
have a meal.

221
00:12:14,630 --> 00:12:16,260
Haven't you told the teacher yet?

222
00:12:17,560 --> 00:12:18,460
About what?

223
00:12:19,070 --> 00:12:20,370
About me.

224
00:12:20,880 --> 00:12:21,780
About how I bullied my classmates,

225
00:12:21,870 --> 00:12:23,530
cheated in the sports meeting,

226
00:12:23,670 --> 00:12:25,890
harassed girls and forced
them to be my deskmates,

227
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:28,220
and fought with your buddy

228
00:12:29,070 --> 00:12:30,930
and put him in the hospital.

229
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:32,490
That's enough to get me expelled.

230
00:12:35,230 --> 00:12:36,580
I don't want to say.

231
00:12:38,630 --> 00:12:40,020
Thank you for your money.

232
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:42,690
It

233
00:12:43,430 --> 00:12:45,620
is very important for
Li Qing Tong's family.

234
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:48,260
I should have taken money.

235
00:12:48,430 --> 00:12:49,980
If you don't have enough
money, then you can tell me.

236
00:12:50,070 --> 00:12:51,270
I will never let Li Qing Tong's family

237
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:52,780
pay a penny for this matter.

238
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:54,220
That's enough.

239
00:12:54,830 --> 00:12:56,250
Besides,

240
00:12:56,430 --> 00:12:59,210
Li Qing Tong was hospitalized
for acute appendicitis.

241
00:13:00,110 --> 00:13:02,090
It has nothing to do with your push.

242
00:13:02,880 --> 00:13:04,340
It's a coincidence.

243
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:06,490
So

244
00:13:06,760 --> 00:13:08,940
I'll definitely find a way to
give you the money back.

245
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:10,290
Don't pay me back.

246
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:14,030
Whatever the reason,

247
00:13:14,120 --> 00:13:15,540
I'm responsible for what I did.

248
00:13:16,030 --> 00:13:17,510
For the past two semesters,

249
00:13:17,590 --> 00:13:20,060
Li Qing Tong has experienced
a lot of scolding due to me,

250
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:22,460
and her reputation at
school has also been ruined.

251
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:24,730
I do owe her.

252
00:13:27,510 --> 00:13:29,630
I know I have a bad character,

253
00:13:29,710 --> 00:13:30,890
and have a bad fortune.

254
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:32,820
But

255
00:13:33,630 --> 00:13:35,020
I didn't bully her.

256
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:37,540
Nor did I do anything to
bully her on purpose.

257
00:13:38,390 --> 00:13:39,740
Later,

258
00:13:40,870 --> 00:13:42,060
I'll be a good boy.

259
00:13:43,430 --> 00:13:45,460
But if you let me away from her,

260
00:13:46,270 --> 00:13:47,290
I can't do that.

261
00:13:48,710 --> 00:13:49,910
I can only assure you that

262
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,650
I won't give her any more trouble.

263
00:13:52,990 --> 00:13:54,130
As for the money,

264
00:13:54,670 --> 00:13:56,190
you were always yelling at me that

265
00:13:56,280 --> 00:13:57,530
I had a vendetta against you.

266
00:13:58,750 --> 00:14:00,410
I owe you both.

267
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:12,370
Are you not going to
take two more days off?

268
00:14:12,830 --> 00:14:13,710
No.

269
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:16,570
I'd like to go back to class early.

270
00:14:20,680 --> 00:14:22,290
Dad, you're back.

271
00:14:23,230 --> 00:14:24,110
Yes, I'm back.

272
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:26,970
You two are still up?

273
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:29,730
Yes.

274
00:14:30,310 --> 00:14:31,190
Well.

275
00:14:31,680 --> 00:14:32,560
Dad.

276
00:14:33,510 --> 00:14:34,390
What's up?

277
00:14:36,520 --> 00:14:38,990
What have you been busy with lately?

278
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:40,500
You've been late every day.

279
00:14:41,750 --> 00:14:42,630
The...

280
00:14:43,510 --> 00:14:44,590
The factory is busy.

281
00:14:44,680 --> 00:14:45,700
It's so busy.

282
00:14:45,790 --> 00:14:46,350
I

283
00:14:46,440 --> 00:14:47,660
am a leader,

284
00:14:47,760 --> 00:14:48,890
so I have to take the lead.

285
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:50,130
Where is your mum?

286
00:14:51,070 --> 00:14:52,610
Maybe she was sleeping.

287
00:14:53,040 --> 00:14:53,660
Well.

288
00:14:53,750 --> 00:14:55,220
I see her.

289
00:15:08,830 --> 00:15:09,790
Hua.

290
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:12,010
Go out to have a breath with me.

291
00:15:13,840 --> 00:15:15,290
What's the matter with you?

292
00:15:19,440 --> 00:15:21,490
Do you know what day it is today?

293
00:15:22,230 --> 00:15:23,500
Which day?

294
00:15:26,190 --> 00:15:27,820
It's my birthday.

295
00:15:29,190 --> 00:15:30,460
Today?

296
00:15:33,710 --> 00:15:35,060
I forgot it.

297
00:15:36,990 --> 00:15:38,930
My parents used to

298
00:15:39,070 --> 00:15:42,130
prepare me a big cake
for my birthday every year.

299
00:15:43,590 --> 00:15:45,770
But they all seem to
have forgotten my birthday.

300
00:15:48,510 --> 00:15:51,530
Maybe they have been busy lately.

301
00:15:52,310 --> 00:15:53,810
Don't think too much about it.

302
00:16:00,480 --> 00:16:02,410
My father's factory closed down.

303
00:16:04,760 --> 00:16:07,370
But he still goes out early
and comes home late.

304
00:16:07,710 --> 00:16:09,570
He seems to be more tired than before.

305
00:16:11,160 --> 00:16:14,580
He doesn't want to
tell me what he's doing.

306
00:16:17,590 --> 00:16:20,060
Adults may have some secret sorrow.

307
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:23,740
As for your birthday,

308
00:16:23,830 --> 00:16:25,230
forget it.

309
00:16:25,310 --> 00:16:26,660
You are one year younger.

310
00:16:30,910 --> 00:16:32,820
How about your birthday?

311
00:16:34,550 --> 00:16:36,090
I never had a birthday,

312
00:16:37,590 --> 00:16:39,170
Why?

313
00:16:40,470 --> 00:16:41,930
No one had been with me.

314
00:16:42,110 --> 00:16:44,650
It is only a kind of ceremony,

315
00:16:44,950 --> 00:16:46,140
so I give it up.

316
00:16:46,630 --> 00:16:47,910
What about your mum?

317
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:49,460
Your mum won't stay with you either?

318
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:52,250
My mum

319
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:57,010
was very busy.

320
00:16:57,510 --> 00:16:59,370
I'm not the only one in her world.

321
00:17:00,950 --> 00:17:02,780
Your mum was busy, too.

322
00:17:08,950 --> 00:17:11,290
It seems that it's not
easy in adults' world.

323
00:17:21,710 --> 00:17:22,589
Mum and Dad seem to be asleep.

324
00:17:22,680 --> 00:17:24,010
Keep your voice down.

325
00:17:38,960 --> 00:17:39,970
Hello!

326
00:17:41,310 --> 00:17:43,030
Dad, what are you doing?

327
00:17:43,110 --> 00:17:45,060
Celebrating my daughter's birthday.

328
00:17:45,150 --> 00:17:45,940
Come here!

329
00:17:46,030 --> 00:17:47,010
Here.

330
00:17:52,840 --> 00:17:55,460
I thought you all forgot.

331
00:17:55,590 --> 00:17:56,580
We can't.

332
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:57,820
As for your birthday,

333
00:17:57,910 --> 00:17:59,890
I have to apologize to you.

334
00:18:00,320 --> 00:18:02,070
You mum reminded me about it
two days ago

335
00:18:02,160 --> 00:18:03,770
and asked me to buy
a birthday cake for you.

336
00:18:04,430 --> 00:18:05,650
But in the past two days,

337
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:06,730
I was so busy.

338
00:18:06,870 --> 00:18:08,930
It's too late to get off work today,

339
00:18:09,190 --> 00:18:10,810
so the cake shop is closed.

340
00:18:11,270 --> 00:18:12,460
And my daughter,

341
00:18:12,550 --> 00:18:13,580
your mum,

342
00:18:13,670 --> 00:18:16,330
didn't feel well these
days and went to bed early.

343
00:18:16,430 --> 00:18:18,060
So I don't tell her

344
00:18:18,150 --> 00:18:19,820
to celebrate your birthday.

345
00:18:19,910 --> 00:18:21,290
Don't blame your parents.

346
00:18:21,510 --> 00:18:22,570
No, no.

347
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:24,070
As for my birthday,

348
00:18:24,150 --> 00:18:25,090
it's fine to not celebrate.

349
00:18:25,280 --> 00:18:26,510
That won't work,

350
00:18:26,600 --> 00:18:29,270
and it can be regarded
as your 18th birthday.

351
00:18:29,360 --> 00:18:30,460
We must celebrate it.

352
00:18:32,350 --> 00:18:35,500
Let's sing a birthday song,

353
00:18:35,840 --> 00:18:37,890
make a wish and blow a candle.

354
00:18:39,870 --> 00:18:40,470
Come.

355
00:18:40,550 --> 00:18:44,380
♫ Happy Birthday to you! ♫

356
00:18:44,470 --> 00:18:48,190
♫ Happy Birthday to you! ♫

357
00:18:48,280 --> 00:18:52,370
♫ Happy Birthday to you! ♫

358
00:18:52,560 --> 00:18:57,890
♫ Happy Birthday to you! ♫

359
00:18:58,790 --> 00:19:00,410
Happy Birthday!

360
00:19:00,950 --> 00:19:02,820
Happy Birthday! My daughter.

361
00:19:03,040 --> 00:19:03,860
Well.

362
00:19:03,950 --> 00:19:05,260
Next,

363
00:19:05,350 --> 00:19:09,130
Let's try Mr Li's special cream cake.

364
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:12,770
Enjoy it, my daughter.

365
00:19:13,110 --> 00:19:15,050
You dipped in honey to eat.

366
00:19:17,030 --> 00:19:17,910
Hua,

367
00:19:18,200 --> 00:19:19,330
you also eat one piece of cake.

368
00:19:21,280 --> 00:19:22,180
How about it?

369
00:19:22,550 --> 00:19:23,450
Is it delicious?

370
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:24,480
Absolutely!

371
00:19:28,950 --> 00:19:30,740
Very good!

372
00:19:33,990 --> 00:19:34,870
Dad,

373
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:38,090
I will be admitted by a university.

374
00:19:39,630 --> 00:19:41,260
You've changed after your birthday.

375
00:19:41,350 --> 00:19:42,260
You have grown up.

376
00:19:42,350 --> 00:19:43,420
I trust you.

377
00:19:47,920 --> 00:19:48,820
Dad,

378
00:19:50,630 --> 00:19:52,730
you always work overtime these days,

379
00:19:54,270 --> 00:19:55,300
so

380
00:19:55,590 --> 00:19:57,020
you should look after your body.

381
00:19:57,110 --> 00:19:58,580
It's okay.

382
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:01,380
What does it mean to work overtime?

383
00:20:01,470 --> 00:20:03,250
It means dad makes money.

384
00:20:04,030 --> 00:20:05,310
I'm discussing it

385
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:06,510
with your mum.

386
00:20:06,590 --> 00:20:08,980
Before you go to university,

387
00:20:09,070 --> 00:20:10,270
we both work hard

388
00:20:10,360 --> 00:20:11,740
to make more money.

389
00:20:11,830 --> 00:20:14,890
This can make my daughter
in an easy way in college.

390
00:20:15,080 --> 00:20:16,250
I know

391
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:17,940
you care about dad.

392
00:20:18,550 --> 00:20:19,460
Now you

393
00:20:19,550 --> 00:20:21,260
just study hard.

394
00:20:21,480 --> 00:20:23,020
Don't think about anything else.

395
00:20:24,190 --> 00:20:25,100
Okay?

396
00:20:28,960 --> 00:20:29,840
Dad.

397
00:20:30,190 --> 00:20:31,980
Actually, a few days ago in hospital, I...

398
00:20:32,070 --> 00:20:32,860
It's 12 o'clock.

399
00:20:32,950 --> 00:20:34,730
Finish your noodles.

400
00:20:35,510 --> 00:20:36,110
Wait for me.

401
00:20:36,190 --> 00:20:37,490
I'll heat it up for you.

402
00:20:38,150 --> 00:20:39,650
It has to be perfect.

403
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:48,930
What wish did you just make?

404
00:20:52,600 --> 00:20:55,170
I hope my parents are healthy.

405
00:21:04,160 --> 00:21:04,830
Tong.

406
00:21:04,910 --> 00:21:05,970
Why are you back?

407
00:21:06,310 --> 00:21:07,610
I'm fine.

408
00:21:08,190 --> 00:21:09,150
You're fine.

409
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:10,790
Then we have to make arrangements tonight

410
00:21:10,880 --> 00:21:11,810
to do something for you.

411
00:21:12,150 --> 00:21:13,950
Don't waste money.

412
00:21:14,030 --> 00:21:14,910
Well,

413
00:21:15,750 --> 00:21:17,630
let's not waste money by
eating and drinking all day.

414
00:21:17,720 --> 00:21:18,910
Do you make money?

415
00:21:18,990 --> 00:21:20,790
Why do you spend your
parents' money all day long?

416
00:21:20,880 --> 00:21:22,170
You should study hard.

417
00:21:30,680 --> 00:21:33,670
Let's go to the library
for self-study tonight.

418
00:21:33,760 --> 00:21:35,420
It's quiet there and we
can learn a little longer.

419
00:21:36,080 --> 00:21:36,960
OK.

420
00:21:37,150 --> 00:21:38,250
What's up?

421
00:21:39,280 --> 00:21:42,340
Hua has never been stingy
before with eating and drinking.

422
00:21:42,510 --> 00:21:43,710
Li Qing Tong is even crazier.

423
00:21:43,800 --> 00:21:45,690
She actually took the initiative to study.

424
00:21:46,030 --> 00:21:47,130
What's going on?

425
00:21:48,110 --> 00:21:49,250
I don't know.

426
00:21:52,360 --> 00:21:55,350
[Tieyuan No. 3 Middle School]

427
00:22:01,990 --> 00:22:03,140
I didn't beat Li Jin Bu,

428
00:22:03,710 --> 00:22:05,170
but I admit it's all my fault.

429
00:22:07,950 --> 00:22:10,250
Chen Jun He, I'm so scared of you.

430
00:22:10,550 --> 00:22:12,140
I'm not as scared as you think.

431
00:22:12,230 --> 00:22:14,500
I don't want to fight like I used to.

432
00:22:14,920 --> 00:22:16,670
I want to study hard now,

433
00:22:16,750 --> 00:22:19,130
and be admitted by a good
university to reward everyone.

434
00:22:19,910 --> 00:22:21,330
Can you let me go?

435
00:23:05,080 --> 00:23:05,980
Just this,

436
00:23:06,080 --> 00:23:07,510
an event

437
00:23:07,590 --> 00:23:10,580
ended with Chen Jun He's
disarming and surrendering.

438
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:12,700
Did he hit you?

439
00:23:14,320 --> 00:23:16,610
A student reported our
conflict on the rooftop,

440
00:23:17,030 --> 00:23:18,810
but Li Qing Tong firmly denied it.

441
00:23:18,960 --> 00:23:21,260
So the school can't dismiss Chen Jun He.

442
00:23:29,080 --> 00:23:30,860
He behaves well after that.

443
00:23:31,080 --> 00:23:33,830
Although he still deliberately
gets close to Li Qing Tong,

444
00:23:33,920 --> 00:23:36,410
he no longer steps out of line.

445
00:23:55,040 --> 00:23:56,190
Li Qing Tong

446
00:23:56,280 --> 00:23:57,650
has changed a lot.

447
00:23:57,830 --> 00:24:00,370
She took it upon herself
to study.

448
00:24:05,310 --> 00:24:07,580
And so, time went by uneventfully.

449
00:24:07,720 --> 00:24:09,540
In the silent classroom
of the twelfth grade,

450
00:24:09,630 --> 00:24:11,470
there was only the sound
of turning over the pages

451
00:24:11,560 --> 00:24:13,460
and the pen strokes across the paper.

452
00:24:13,550 --> 00:24:14,700
Thousands of miles of wind
blowing south swan goose,

453
00:24:14,790 --> 00:24:17,270
in the face of this scene, you
can climb a tall building to drink.

454
00:24:17,350 --> 00:24:19,030
All the brilliant heroes
for thousands of years...

455
00:24:19,110 --> 00:24:19,870
So the west side of the base...

456
00:24:19,870 --> 00:24:21,500
[Tieyuan No. 3 Middle School]

457
00:24:21,500 --> 00:24:23,440
[Countdown: 186]

458
00:24:23,480 --> 00:24:25,820
[Countdown: 157]

459
00:24:26,700 --> 00:24:28,730
[Countdown: 138]

460
00:24:34,070 --> 00:24:34,950
Wake up and learn.

461
00:24:36,710 --> 00:24:36,830
Everyone is under the pressure of
the college entrance examination.

462
00:24:36,830 --> 00:24:40,160
[Countdown]

463
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:41,530
Until one day,

464
00:24:41,830 --> 00:24:42,130
an announcement

465
00:24:42,130 --> 00:24:43,240
[Tieyuan No. 3 Middle School.
Notice]

466
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:45,350
once again made the class restless.

467
00:24:45,440 --> 00:24:51,270
The school will hold its 20th
Anniversary Arts Festival next month.

468
00:24:51,350 --> 00:24:56,460
The participating classes are urged
to prepare their programmes in advance.

469
00:25:00,030 --> 00:25:02,570
Our class isn't on the list
of participating classes.

470
00:25:02,750 --> 00:25:04,530
We've been excluded.

471
00:25:04,920 --> 00:25:06,140
Well,

472
00:25:06,430 --> 00:25:07,620
we are even not allowed to take PE class,

473
00:25:07,710 --> 00:25:09,370
not to mention the Arts Festival.

474
00:25:11,320 --> 00:25:12,310
What a pity

475
00:25:12,400 --> 00:25:15,290
for my sexy, Jacky Cheung-like
singing voice.

476
00:25:16,310 --> 00:25:17,490
Nonsense.

477
00:25:17,630 --> 00:25:19,170
Don't ruin Jacky Cheung's song.

478
00:25:19,320 --> 00:25:21,050
You can't even speak properly.

479
00:25:23,080 --> 00:25:24,570
What?

480
00:25:27,310 --> 00:25:28,190
Sir.

481
00:25:29,030 --> 00:25:29,910
Come in.

482
00:25:32,990 --> 00:25:33,870
What's up?

483
00:25:34,030 --> 00:25:35,130
Mr Wu,

484
00:25:35,430 --> 00:25:36,940
I think it's unfair.

485
00:25:37,430 --> 00:25:38,530
What?

486
00:25:38,630 --> 00:25:39,660
I don't think school will deprive us of

487
00:25:39,750 --> 00:25:41,850
the right to participate in
literary and artistic performances.

488
00:25:42,830 --> 00:25:44,820
The rules are all set
by the school leaders.

489
00:25:44,910 --> 00:25:47,410
Twelfth grade students have
always been not to participate in.

490
00:25:47,550 --> 00:25:49,530
Time is too tight and we
don't have enough energy.

491
00:25:50,110 --> 00:25:52,030
But it's a school activity.

492
00:25:52,120 --> 00:25:53,300
We are in the graduating class,

493
00:25:53,390 --> 00:25:56,050
and catch such a memorable activity.

494
00:25:56,150 --> 00:25:58,530
Can't school give us a chance?

495
00:26:01,110 --> 00:26:01,510
Alright.

496
00:26:01,600 --> 00:26:02,900
Then,

497
00:26:03,190 --> 00:26:04,030
about the Arts Festival activity,

498
00:26:04,120 --> 00:26:06,330
I'll communicate with the leader again.

499
00:26:06,880 --> 00:26:07,810
Thanks, sir.

500
00:26:07,960 --> 00:26:08,840
Go back.

501
00:26:12,600 --> 00:26:13,480
No,

502
00:26:15,270 --> 00:26:16,150
Mr Wu,

503
00:26:16,790 --> 00:26:18,060
there are no classes in the twelfth grade

504
00:26:18,150 --> 00:26:20,940
that ask to attend except your class.

505
00:26:21,030 --> 00:26:23,290
Why is your class so restless?

506
00:26:23,510 --> 00:26:25,020
Director, playing combines with studying.

507
00:26:25,950 --> 00:26:27,820
We can't keep the
children on a leash all the time.

508
00:26:27,910 --> 00:26:29,020
We give them less pressure,

509
00:26:29,110 --> 00:26:30,420
and we should give them more pressure.

510
00:26:31,030 --> 00:26:31,910
Mr Wu,

511
00:26:32,080 --> 00:26:36,020
you can't think about everything
from the students' point of view.

512
00:26:36,150 --> 00:26:37,930
It's your first time to be the head
teacher of the graduating class,

513
00:26:38,030 --> 00:26:39,420
so you have to

514
00:26:39,670 --> 00:26:40,930
be more careful.

515
00:26:41,670 --> 00:26:42,550
I know.

516
00:26:44,040 --> 00:26:45,070
Well, you go about your business,

517
00:26:45,160 --> 00:26:46,290
I'll go first.

518
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:15,100
I have a little proposal.

519
00:27:15,870 --> 00:27:16,810
What?

520
00:27:17,520 --> 00:27:18,700
I think

521
00:27:19,160 --> 00:27:21,610
communication between
people is particularly important.

522
00:27:22,150 --> 00:27:23,590
We should communicate frequently

523
00:27:23,680 --> 00:27:24,940
to truly improve

524
00:27:25,030 --> 00:27:26,420
and to get benefit.

525
00:27:28,280 --> 00:27:29,330
And then?

526
00:27:30,870 --> 00:27:32,510
I mean,

527
00:27:32,600 --> 00:27:35,690
can we get along like
friends in the future?

528
00:27:37,320 --> 00:27:38,890
Before studying,

529
00:27:39,230 --> 00:27:40,850
let's talk for five minutes first.

530
00:27:42,870 --> 00:27:43,900
Talk what?

531
00:27:44,240 --> 00:27:45,290
Everything.

532
00:27:45,830 --> 00:27:47,540
What you see and hear,

533
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:49,690
your love and hate, everything.

534
00:27:51,230 --> 00:27:52,110
OK.

535
00:27:53,990 --> 00:27:54,540
I'll talk to you first.

536
00:27:54,630 --> 00:27:56,230
From the moment you started talking,

537
00:27:56,310 --> 00:27:57,900
it's been five minutes now.

538
00:27:58,270 --> 00:27:59,620
Today's chat is over.

539
00:27:59,710 --> 00:28:00,590
Do your work.

540
00:28:14,350 --> 00:28:15,970
I'll ask everyone a question before class.

541
00:28:16,390 --> 00:28:18,370
Who wants to take part in the
literary and artistic performance?

542
00:28:19,190 --> 00:28:20,340
Raise your hand, please.

543
00:28:20,470 --> 00:28:21,350
Let me see.

544
00:28:25,910 --> 00:28:27,010
Only two.

545
00:28:28,510 --> 00:28:29,390
Anyone else?

546
00:29:02,870 --> 00:29:03,270
Well, put your hands down.

547
00:29:03,360 --> 00:29:03,790
I get it.

548
00:29:03,870 --> 00:29:04,900
Take class first.

549
00:29:36,190 --> 00:29:37,140
Come in.

550
00:29:43,320 --> 00:29:45,060
Why are you so active?

551
00:29:45,400 --> 00:29:47,650
Does this Arts Festival
have anything to do with us?

552
00:29:48,800 --> 00:29:51,050
It's the school's 20th anniversary.

553
00:29:52,910 --> 00:29:54,770
We're going to graduate from this school.

554
00:29:54,870 --> 00:29:56,570
Do you want to leave a good memory?

555
00:29:57,750 --> 00:30:00,580
But it's not easy for you
to get into a state of study,

556
00:30:00,680 --> 00:30:02,030
and we'll take the college entrance exam.

557
00:30:02,120 --> 00:30:02,740
Now,

558
00:30:02,830 --> 00:30:04,580
Hua, please trust me.

559
00:30:04,670 --> 00:30:07,300
I won't let it affect my studies.

560
00:30:07,790 --> 00:30:09,100
I just want to put on

561
00:30:09,190 --> 00:30:11,610
a spectacular performance with everyone
for once.

562
00:30:11,950 --> 00:30:13,020
At least

563
00:30:13,270 --> 00:30:14,730
for old time's sake.

564
00:30:15,390 --> 00:30:16,490
Big news!

565
00:30:17,230 --> 00:30:17,670
What?

566
00:30:17,760 --> 00:30:18,630
Mr Wu

567
00:30:18,720 --> 00:30:19,780
went to the headmaster's office

568
00:30:19,870 --> 00:30:21,500
to plead for us.

569
00:30:22,360 --> 00:30:23,410
Really?

570
00:30:24,470 --> 00:30:25,350
Go!

571
00:30:26,390 --> 00:30:28,010
Don't hang around.

572
00:30:31,480 --> 00:30:33,380
Go out, go out.

573
00:30:45,870 --> 00:30:47,180
Go, go.

574
00:30:47,270 --> 00:30:48,860
What's up?

575
00:30:56,270 --> 00:30:57,390
Don't make any noise.

576
00:30:57,480 --> 00:30:59,020
Go, go, go.

577
00:31:06,480 --> 00:31:08,460
Keep quiet!

578
00:31:09,910 --> 00:31:11,250
I tell you

579
00:31:11,640 --> 00:31:13,020
that I bet on my face

580
00:31:13,110 --> 00:31:14,530
and asked the headmaster for help.

581
00:31:15,110 --> 00:31:16,220
You have to thank me.

582
00:31:16,310 --> 00:31:17,270
Got it?

583
00:31:17,360 --> 00:31:19,210
Got it.

584
00:31:19,360 --> 00:31:20,230
But

585
00:31:20,310 --> 00:31:21,690
there are some conditions.

586
00:31:21,910 --> 00:31:24,250
That's one of the biggest reasons
I convinced the headmaster.

587
00:31:24,880 --> 00:31:25,900
If you can't do that,

588
00:31:25,990 --> 00:31:27,330
there's nothing I can do.

589
00:31:27,720 --> 00:31:28,510
Just tell us.

590
00:31:28,600 --> 00:31:30,530
No matter what the condition is,
we'll do it.

591
00:31:32,190 --> 00:31:33,070
30 points.

592
00:31:33,470 --> 00:31:34,540
Those of you

593
00:31:34,710 --> 00:31:37,510
who scored below 550 on the second test

594
00:31:37,590 --> 00:31:39,010
must improve by 30 points.

595
00:31:39,230 --> 00:31:41,140
Only then are we allowed
to participate in the performance.

596
00:31:43,710 --> 00:31:44,980
I understand that

597
00:31:45,150 --> 00:31:47,460
Wu Zhi Xun is the only one in our class
who scored more than 550.

598
00:31:47,550 --> 00:31:48,950
That means the rest of us

599
00:31:49,030 --> 00:31:50,900
must improve by 30 points
in the third test.

600
00:31:50,990 --> 00:31:52,260
Lack of one student won't work.

601
00:31:52,830 --> 00:31:55,500
It's obviously not to let us do that.

602
00:31:55,590 --> 00:31:56,910
We're now in twelfth grade,

603
00:31:57,000 --> 00:31:58,260
and the college entrance
examination is approaching.

604
00:31:58,350 --> 00:31:59,990
If you don't show any
strength to prove your ability,

605
00:32:00,080 --> 00:32:01,020
the school can't

606
00:32:01,110 --> 00:32:03,030
let you take part in the performance.

607
00:32:03,110 --> 00:32:04,140
Isn't that right?

608
00:32:04,310 --> 00:32:05,290
As the old saying goes,

609
00:32:05,680 --> 00:32:07,610
you can't have both
the fish and the bear palm.

610
00:32:08,070 --> 00:32:09,140
If you want both,

611
00:32:09,230 --> 00:32:11,130
then you should have the ambition.

612
00:32:11,430 --> 00:32:12,310
If you study hard,

613
00:32:12,400 --> 00:32:13,590
I believe

614
00:32:13,670 --> 00:32:14,220
we

615
00:32:14,310 --> 00:32:15,540
have the potential

616
00:32:15,630 --> 00:32:17,380
to be the first class in
No. 3 Middle School

617
00:32:17,470 --> 00:32:19,100
to break this rule.

618
00:32:19,320 --> 00:32:20,690
If you can't do that,

619
00:32:21,110 --> 00:32:22,420
I have no other ways to help you.

620
00:32:23,870 --> 00:32:25,060
This is the twelfth grade,

621
00:32:25,510 --> 00:32:28,020
and no one dares to
gamble with your senior year.

622
00:32:30,270 --> 00:32:31,150
What's up?

623
00:32:32,640 --> 00:32:33,860
You want to give up?

624
00:32:35,080 --> 00:32:35,960
Well,

625
00:32:36,190 --> 00:32:37,390
I will tell the headmaster that

626
00:32:37,480 --> 00:32:39,150
you don't have the ambition.

627
00:32:39,240 --> 00:32:41,020
Sir, we'd like to do that.

628
00:32:46,190 --> 00:32:48,730
Although I can't represent you all,

629
00:32:49,480 --> 00:32:50,740
I think that

630
00:32:50,830 --> 00:32:53,250
none of our classmates are so timid.

631
00:32:53,670 --> 00:32:55,430
I'm the bottom-ranking one in class,

632
00:32:55,520 --> 00:32:57,140
and If I think I can do that,

633
00:32:57,230 --> 00:32:58,890
everyone can do that.

634
00:33:05,270 --> 00:33:05,940
Can I get some reaction?

635
00:33:06,030 --> 00:33:06,930
You.

636
00:33:07,520 --> 00:33:08,190
Well, sit down.

637
00:33:08,280 --> 00:33:09,750
You decide it by yourselves after class.

638
00:33:09,840 --> 00:33:10,730
Listen to your class first.

639
00:33:15,570 --> 00:33:18,640
[Daily Necessity Supermarket
and Restaurant]

640
00:33:18,640 --> 00:33:22,140
I want to do something crazy in the show.

641
00:33:22,510 --> 00:33:24,050
Now there's no chance.

642
00:33:25,030 --> 00:33:26,020
That's not for sure.

643
00:33:26,120 --> 00:33:27,430
I think if we work hard,

644
00:33:27,510 --> 00:33:28,860
we have a chance.

645
00:33:29,960 --> 00:33:31,180
How do we work hard?

646
00:33:31,910 --> 00:33:33,730
It's 30 points we're talking about.

647
00:33:34,040 --> 00:33:36,420
It's hard enough for me
not to drop by 30 points.

648
00:33:36,510 --> 00:33:38,430
Do you want to be looked
down upon by the school?

649
00:33:38,510 --> 00:33:40,050
Try your best.

650
00:33:40,150 --> 00:33:42,020
We can't have the ability.

651
00:33:42,110 --> 00:33:43,460
But we should have a try.

652
00:33:43,550 --> 00:33:44,980
Can we admit defeat so easily?

653
00:33:45,070 --> 00:33:46,020
I agree.

654
00:33:48,590 --> 00:33:49,660
Why are you looking at me?

655
00:33:49,950 --> 00:33:52,020
I'm not just urging Li Qing Tong to learn,

656
00:33:52,110 --> 00:33:53,690
but I am also reasonable.

657
00:33:54,190 --> 00:33:57,460
I think Li Qing Tong has proved
herself and is willing to work hard.

658
00:33:57,630 --> 00:33:59,930
I'll support her in doing
what she wants to do.

659
00:34:00,270 --> 00:34:01,780
Hua, you're so kind.

660
00:34:03,080 --> 00:34:06,010
But the most important
thing now is not our attitude,

661
00:34:06,430 --> 00:34:08,510
it's about getting the whole
class to work together.

662
00:34:08,600 --> 00:34:10,659
So we will have the opportunity.

663
00:34:13,150 --> 00:34:14,050
You're right.

664
00:34:14,199 --> 00:34:16,210
As you can see from their attitude,

665
00:34:16,310 --> 00:34:17,570
they all have no confidence.

666
00:34:19,429 --> 00:34:20,540
Let's study hard together,

667
00:34:20,630 --> 00:34:21,989
and give our classmates confidence

668
00:34:22,070 --> 00:34:23,050
to fight for the opportunity.

669
00:34:23,150 --> 00:34:26,300
[Tieyuan No. 3 Middle School]

670
00:34:32,560 --> 00:34:33,900
Everybody, stop!

671
00:34:34,320 --> 00:34:37,070
I have something to tell you before class.

672
00:34:37,150 --> 00:34:39,380
I hope you can give me a chance.

673
00:34:42,989 --> 00:34:44,659
This is a petition,

674
00:34:44,800 --> 00:34:46,050
and its content is simple.

675
00:34:46,440 --> 00:34:48,230
All the students in Class Three

676
00:34:48,320 --> 00:34:50,389
are willing to improve their
test scores by 30

677
00:34:50,469 --> 00:34:52,730
for a chance to attend
the School Anniversary.

678
00:34:54,159 --> 00:34:56,020
I know it's very difficult.

679
00:34:56,590 --> 00:34:57,740
Mr Wu said that

680
00:34:57,830 --> 00:34:59,610
we can't have both the fish
and the bear palm.

681
00:35:00,030 --> 00:35:02,300
But just because it's difficult,
we won't be able to do it?

682
00:35:02,430 --> 00:35:04,590
Can't we try to do it?

683
00:35:04,670 --> 00:35:06,930
Can't we try to do it together?

684
00:35:07,390 --> 00:35:09,170
Before coming to this class,

685
00:35:09,590 --> 00:35:11,130
I  didn't have a friend at all.

686
00:35:11,350 --> 00:35:13,620
I don't talk much to anyone.

687
00:35:14,070 --> 00:35:15,260
But,

688
00:35:15,360 --> 00:35:16,930
when I came to this class,

689
00:35:17,480 --> 00:35:19,690
I think each of you was particularly kind.

690
00:35:22,400 --> 00:35:23,260
I still remember

691
00:35:23,350 --> 00:35:25,590
Li Qiang lent me a piece of eraser,

692
00:35:25,670 --> 00:35:26,820
but I lost it.

693
00:35:27,070 --> 00:35:28,150
He didn't blame me,

694
00:35:28,240 --> 00:35:29,900
instead, I was given
another piece of eraser.

695
00:35:30,440 --> 00:35:32,010
I remember

696
00:35:32,350 --> 00:35:34,700
Lei Jiang saw me carrying
a bucket of water

697
00:35:34,790 --> 00:35:37,090
and offered to help me carry it
all the way back to the class.

698
00:35:37,310 --> 00:35:38,770
Another time I had a cold,

699
00:35:38,990 --> 00:35:42,050
Zhao Xiao Na brought me her family's
home remedy for three days in a row.

700
00:35:44,150 --> 00:35:46,420
And when I hurt my leg,

701
00:35:46,640 --> 00:35:48,450
Lin Xue Wei offered to help me
with my duty,

702
00:35:48,990 --> 00:35:50,580
and swept the whole corridor

703
00:35:50,680 --> 00:35:52,490
for 40 minutes.

704
00:35:52,830 --> 00:35:55,450
And when we played
tug-of-war in the eleventh grade,

705
00:35:55,670 --> 00:35:58,130
the group of boys in the
twelfth grade rushed up,

706
00:35:58,470 --> 00:36:00,830
and all the boys in our class
stood in front of the girls.

707
00:36:00,920 --> 00:36:02,930
We, the girls, didn't even get any dust
on us.

708
00:36:03,120 --> 00:36:04,140
So,

709
00:36:04,710 --> 00:36:06,450
no matter what other people think of us,

710
00:36:06,670 --> 00:36:08,230
whether they think we're disobedient,

711
00:36:08,320 --> 00:36:10,220
incapable,

712
00:36:10,310 --> 00:36:12,150
always coming in last in competitions
and fights,

713
00:36:12,230 --> 00:36:15,490
or wasting our time on the Anniversary
when the exams are so near,

714
00:36:16,150 --> 00:36:18,140
everyone thinks we're a joke.

715
00:36:18,230 --> 00:36:19,450
But I know,

716
00:36:19,550 --> 00:36:21,090
we're not a joke.

717
00:36:21,400 --> 00:36:23,030
The boys in our class are gentlemen,

718
00:36:23,110 --> 00:36:24,610
and the girls are very kind.

719
00:36:24,800 --> 00:36:28,010
We cherish every day we spend together.

720
00:36:30,910 --> 00:36:31,990
So,

721
00:36:32,080 --> 00:36:34,820
when Mr Wu asked if any of us
wanted to participate in the Anniversary,

722
00:36:35,160 --> 00:36:36,850
everyone raised their hands.

723
00:36:39,950 --> 00:36:41,980
But no one forced us to raise our hands.

724
00:36:43,790 --> 00:36:45,630
If you have the same idea as me,

725
00:36:45,720 --> 00:36:47,580
just sign your name
on this piece of paper.

726
00:36:48,560 --> 00:36:50,780
We use action to prove it to the teacher.

727
00:36:51,470 --> 00:36:54,700
We are not just worth doing simple things,

728
00:36:54,790 --> 00:36:55,580
we can do

729
00:36:55,670 --> 00:36:58,290
what they think we'll never be able to do.

730
00:38:08,030 --> 00:38:08,910
Hua,

731
00:38:09,240 --> 00:38:11,370
I must say some words to you.

732
00:38:11,790 --> 00:38:14,180
I don't expect you to
be able to talk so much.

733
00:38:14,870 --> 00:38:16,850
That almost moved me.

734
00:38:16,950 --> 00:38:17,900
That situation...

735
00:38:18,360 --> 00:38:19,110
That...

736
00:38:19,190 --> 00:38:20,660
what do you mean by almost?

737
00:38:20,790 --> 00:38:22,820
The whole class was moved,

738
00:38:22,910 --> 00:38:25,190
except you, you heartless idiot?

739
00:38:25,280 --> 00:38:25,870
No,

740
00:38:25,960 --> 00:38:27,100
it's all in my heart.

741
00:38:27,190 --> 00:38:28,100
Do you understand?

742
00:38:28,190 --> 00:38:29,510
It's called heart-to-heart.

743
00:38:29,600 --> 00:38:30,480
Right?

744
00:38:30,680 --> 00:38:31,350
You've got to be joking.

745
00:38:31,440 --> 00:38:32,320
Hua.

746
00:38:32,470 --> 00:38:33,940
If I have your eloquence,

747
00:38:34,030 --> 00:38:35,690
I've been the monitor.

748
00:38:36,110 --> 00:38:37,850
Actually, I'm talking nonsense, too.

749
00:38:38,480 --> 00:38:39,340
I am

750
00:38:39,430 --> 00:38:40,770
very nervous.

751
00:38:41,240 --> 00:38:42,340
Next,

752
00:38:42,830 --> 00:38:44,450
we are facing the most difficult things.

753
00:38:44,760 --> 00:38:45,640
What?

754
00:38:45,830 --> 00:38:46,980
What do you think?

755
00:38:47,550 --> 00:38:48,940
30 points.

756
00:38:49,040 --> 00:38:50,100
It's hard enough for you guys,

757
00:38:50,190 --> 00:38:51,700
let alone the rest of the class.

758
00:38:52,560 --> 00:38:54,340
Shouldn't you think of something?

759
00:38:55,790 --> 00:38:56,670
Never mind.

760
00:38:57,790 --> 00:38:58,940
I have an idea.

761
00:39:05,150 --> 00:39:05,940
Not bad.

762
00:39:06,030 --> 00:39:07,130
You've improved a lot.

763
00:39:08,350 --> 00:39:10,250
It's all thanks to you.

764
00:39:11,230 --> 00:39:13,140
But there's still careless mistakes.

765
00:39:13,630 --> 00:39:14,790
About this last question,

766
00:39:14,870 --> 00:39:15,270
I have taught you this once.

767
00:39:15,360 --> 00:39:16,460
Wait a moment.

768
00:39:18,390 --> 00:39:19,770
Let me ask you a question first.

769
00:39:20,350 --> 00:39:22,620
You see, I'm making so much progress now.

770
00:39:23,070 --> 00:39:24,590
If I want to score

771
00:39:24,670 --> 00:39:25,980
30 points higher

772
00:39:26,070 --> 00:39:27,290
in the next test,

773
00:39:28,320 --> 00:39:29,730
is that possible?

774
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:30,980
You mean the total score?

775
00:39:32,080 --> 00:39:33,450
I don't think it'll be a problem.

776
00:39:37,710 --> 00:39:38,230
I

777
00:39:38,310 --> 00:39:39,900
have a favour to ask of you.

778
00:39:40,270 --> 00:39:41,450
What?

779
00:39:52,590 --> 00:39:53,470
Hello.

780
00:40:00,590 --> 00:40:01,930
Don't go.

781
00:40:04,230 --> 00:40:05,670
Don't say any more.

782
00:40:05,760 --> 00:40:07,870
It's my bottom line to tutor you.

783
00:40:07,960 --> 00:40:10,210
I can't be a teacher for many people.

784
00:40:10,480 --> 00:40:11,470
I don't have that energy

785
00:40:11,560 --> 00:40:12,540
and that obligation.

786
00:40:12,630 --> 00:40:14,350
You don't really need to tutor them.

787
00:40:14,440 --> 00:40:15,990
They have a better foundation than me.

788
00:40:16,080 --> 00:40:17,630
Just let them sit in.

789
00:40:17,710 --> 00:40:18,940
I'll say it again.

790
00:40:19,030 --> 00:40:19,660
No

791
00:40:19,750 --> 00:40:20,700
means no.

792
00:40:21,280 --> 00:40:22,410
Wait a moment.

793
00:40:24,120 --> 00:40:25,850
Don't be so angry.

794
00:40:25,950 --> 00:40:27,220
Why?

795
00:40:27,670 --> 00:40:28,950
You know it, too.

796
00:40:29,030 --> 00:40:30,330
That's precisely the reason.

797
00:40:31,070 --> 00:40:32,060
Li Qing Tong,

798
00:40:32,190 --> 00:40:33,980
I admit that Li Jin Bu makes a good point.

799
00:40:34,070 --> 00:40:36,910
Improving by 30 points
is a good thing for learning.

800
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:38,220
But do you know?

801
00:40:38,320 --> 00:40:40,180
How many days there are left for us
to the college entrance examination?

802
00:40:40,350 --> 00:40:42,420
You can't go to college by
only getting 30 points more.

803
00:40:42,510 --> 00:40:44,910
You must improve by 200
to 300 points.

804
00:40:44,990 --> 00:40:46,020
Do you understand?

805
00:40:46,800 --> 00:40:47,940
Well,

806
00:40:48,030 --> 00:40:49,780
there is no conflict with that.

807
00:40:49,910 --> 00:40:51,190
How is there no conflict?

808
00:40:51,270 --> 00:40:53,650
All you think about now
is the Arts Festival.

809
00:40:54,190 --> 00:40:56,090
You even asked me to help them.

810
00:40:56,240 --> 00:40:58,370
Do you know how I'm helping you now?

811
00:40:58,590 --> 00:41:01,130
Do you really think that notebook is mine?

812
00:41:01,470 --> 00:41:03,830
I wrote it for you word by word.

813
00:41:03,910 --> 00:41:05,660
Everything was written specifically
for your situation.

814
00:41:05,750 --> 00:41:08,300
I spent four to five nights coming up
with the solutions

815
00:41:08,390 --> 00:41:09,730
and strategies.

816
00:41:10,240 --> 00:41:11,730
That's why I want you to memorise them.

817
00:41:14,750 --> 00:41:16,830
I don't have time to do this for them.

818
00:41:16,920 --> 00:41:18,330
But you're different.

819
00:41:18,830 --> 00:41:19,710
You're...

820
00:41:21,880 --> 00:41:23,420
You're the one I'm trying to help.

821
00:41:24,080 --> 00:41:26,010
I don't want all my effort

822
00:41:26,110 --> 00:41:28,330
to be in vain.

823
00:41:28,630 --> 00:41:30,580
So please have a little respect
for me.

824
00:41:31,360 --> 00:41:33,290
I am not a teaching robot.

825
00:41:33,630 --> 00:41:34,510
Alright?

826
00:41:52,480 --> 00:41:54,620
Let's not trouble him.

827
00:41:54,710 --> 00:41:56,220
Let's rely on ourselves.

828
00:41:56,390 --> 00:41:57,550
See? I told you.

829
00:41:57,640 --> 00:41:59,330
Why would he tutor us?

830
00:42:00,910 --> 00:42:01,790
It's okay.

831
00:42:02,160 --> 00:42:03,450
We can rely on ourselves.

832
00:42:15,990 --> 00:42:17,550
Let's do papers together from today.

833
00:42:17,630 --> 00:42:18,620
We solve difficult problems together,

834
00:42:18,710 --> 00:42:20,100
remember difficult points.

835
00:42:42,950 --> 00:42:44,300
Don't eat.

836
00:42:44,840 --> 00:42:45,870
This time, we

837
00:42:45,960 --> 00:42:47,130
must win.

838
00:42:48,070 --> 00:42:49,330
Study.

839
00:42:50,630 --> 00:42:52,340
Answer the first question
of the fill-in-the-blank.

840
00:42:52,560 --> 00:42:54,330
"What about having a drink?"

841
00:42:55,230 --> 00:42:56,420
Four options.

842
00:43:05,200 --> 00:43:06,930
I thought you were not coming today.

843
00:43:20,160 --> 00:43:22,060
For our first five minutes today,

844
00:43:22,800 --> 00:43:24,340
can I listen to you?

845
00:43:28,960 --> 00:43:31,890
Every time, I'm chattering
over these five minutes.

846
00:43:32,430 --> 00:43:34,930
It has to be your turn
this time round, right?

847
00:43:36,070 --> 00:43:37,570
And I think,

848
00:43:39,030 --> 00:43:40,580
when you criticize me,

849
00:43:40,670 --> 00:43:41,890
you say quite a lot of words.

850
